1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Ne5 Nc6 5. d4 e6 $5 {Beginning of a
strategy to develop the knight to e7 after ...Bd6 and play ...f7-f6 eventually}
6. c3 ({A more critical line is} 6. Bb5 Qc7 7. Bf4 Bd6 8. Qg4 Kf8 9. Bxc6 Nf6
$1 10. Qf3 bxc6 $13 {1/2-1/2 (41) Lupulescu,C (2619)-Swapnil,S (2487) Abu
Dhabi 2018}) 6... Bd6 7. f4 Nge7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O f6 {The benefit of
developing the knight to e7 - White cannot count on the usual e5-outpost.} 10.
Qh5 Nf5 11. Nxc6 (11. g4 fxe5 12. fxe5 (12. gxf5 $4 {doesn't work simply
because of} e4 $1 $19) 12... Nxe5 $1 13. dxe5 Bc5+ 14. Kh1 g6 15. Qh3 Nh4 {
and Black is much better.}) 11... bxc6 12. Nd2 (12. Bxf5 $2 exf5 {would be
strategically wrong for White because his white squares are too weak.}) 12...
g6 13. Qe2 (13. Qh3 e5 $1 14. fxe5 fxe5 15. dxe5 Bxe5 $15) 13... Qc7 14. g4 $5
Ng7 15. Nb3 ({Ideally White would like to play} 15. Nf3 {but this doesn't work
because of} Bxf4 16. Bxf4 Qxf4 17. Ne5 Qg5 18. Nxc6 Bd7 $15) 15... Bd7 {
I decided I should prepare e5 as fast as possible. In general Black should
open the position and then White's king can be in danger.} 16. Bd2 (16. c4 $6 {
I spent a lot of time calculating this move, as I was afraid that White would
play c5 and Black might have some problems, but finally realized that I have
the strong reply} e5 $1 17. c5 Be7 18. fxe5 fxe5 19. Rxf8+ (19. Qxe5 Qxe5 20.
dxe5 Rxf1+ 21. Kxf1 Bxg4 $17) 19... Rxf8 20. dxe5 a5 $1 21. a4 Ne6 $17) 16...
Rae8 17. Rae1 e5 18. fxe5 fxe5 19. Rxf8+ Kxf8 20. dxe5 Bxe5 $15 21. Qf3+ Kg8
22. Rf1 $2 {White tries to solve all his problems using tactics, but this
doesn't work.} ({During the game I calculated that White could play something
like} 22. h3 Ne6 23. Rf1 Rf8 24. Qe2 Rxf1+ 25. Kxf1 {and Black is only
slightly better.}) 22... Bxh2+ $1 23. Kg2 Bc8 $1 24. Nd4 ({We both missed} 24.
c4 $5 {and now Black has to find some really difficult moves:} Ne6 $1 (24...
Bd6 25. cxd5 cxd5 26. Nd4 $1 $44 {and apparently White has good compensation,
for example} Qb7 27. Ba6 $1 Qxa6 28. Qf7+ Kh8 29. Bh6 Rg8 30. Re1 Bf8 31. Bxg7+
Rxg7 (31... Bxg7 $4 32. Re8 $18) 32. Qxf8+ Rg8 33. Qf4 $14) 25. Ba5 (25. Bh6
Bd6 26. cxd5 cxd5 $17) 25... Qf4 $1 26. cxd5 cxd5 27. Qh3 Bb7 $3 28. Rxf4 (28.
Nc5 Qe5 $1 29. Nxb7 Nf4+ 30. Rxf4 Bxf4 $17) (28. Qxh2 d4+ 29. Kg1 Qxg4+ 30. Kf2
Nf4 $19) 28... Nxf4+ 29. Kxh2 Nxh3 30. Kxh3 Re3+ 31. Kh4 Rxd3 32. Nc5 Rd4 33.
Nxb7 h5 {and Black has great winning chances.}) 24... Bd6 25. Nxc6 $4 {I'm not
sure, what my opponent missed here. We were already in time-trouble, so maybe
that's why he wanted to complicate matters.} (25. Bf4 Bxf4 26. Qxf4 Qxf4 27.
Rxf4 c5 $17) 25... Qxc6 26. Qf7+ (26. Bxg6 Rf8 $1 (26... hxg6 $4 27. Qf7+ Kh8
28. Rh1+ Nh5 29. Rxh5+ gxh5 30. Qf6+ $1 Kg8 31. Qg6+ $11) 27. Bf7+ Kh8 $19)
26... Kh8 27. Bh6 Rg8 $1 $19 28. Re1 Bf8 29. Rf1 d4+ 30. Kh3 Bxg4+ $1 31. Kxg4
Qg2+ 32. Kh4 Nf5+ (32... Nf5+ 33. Rxf5 (33. Bxf5 g5+ 34. Kh5 Qe2+ $1 35. Bg4
Qh2+ 36. Bh3 Qxh3#) 33... Qh2+ 34. Kg4 gxf5+ $19) 0-1

