{[#]} 10. Bb5+ $1 (10. Nxf5 $6 Nxf5 $11) 10... Nd7 11. Bg5 $1 {A powerful
strategy - White is getting rid of his bishops to secure a permanent outpost
on d4 for his knight.} Bg6 12. h4 h6 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. h5 Bh7 15. O-O O-O 16.
Bxd7 Qxd7 17. Re1 $14 {White has a long term positional advantage. The
centralized knight gives him opportunities to play on both flanks. Black
remains very solid but this is the kind of material balance that we should try
to avoid in this type of position because White can squeeze for a long time.}
Rac8 18. Qd2 Rc4 19. Re3 Rfc8 20. c3 a6 21. a3 Kh8 22. Rae1 Be4 23. f3 Bh7 24.
Kh2 b5 25. g4 a5 26. b3 R4c7 27. Kg3 Rb8 28. Ra1 Qe7 29. b4 Rc4 30. Kh3 Qg5 31.
