{[#]} 22... Qb6 $1 {Anand correctly judged that Black would have better
chances in an equal-looking endgame. Once the queens are off the board, White
has no chances for the attack on the king, while the e5-pawn is likely to
become vulnerable.} ({In case of} 22... b5 23. Nf3 bxa4 24. Ng5 $13 {White
obtains some chances for the kingside attack.}) 23. Qxb6 Nxb6 24. h4 Kf8 25. g3
Ke7 26. b3 Rc7 27. a5 Nd7 28. c4 Rbc8 29. Kg2 Nb8 $1 30. Ra4 Rd8 31. f4 Nc6 $15
{Black has no weaknesses and has better piece coordination.} 0-1

