typical middlegame position for Black as he has developed all his pieces.
There is a slight pressure on the queenside, which could provide us with some
time to prepare a central break.}) 6... Nf6 7. Bg2 Bc5 {Black fights for the
d4-square by developing the bishop to this active diagonal, which is quite
typical for this variation.} 8. O-O Nbd7 {This is the most precise.} (8... O-O
