{This structure occurs after White advances on the Kingside with h2-h4 and
black responds with h7-h6. Important points to remember:- 1. White will try to
gain more space on the kingside with pawn advances h4-h5 and g2-g4. f2-f4 is
also a very likely advance, after which white intends to create attacking
chances on the kingside. 2. All the above pawn advances takes a lot of time
which Black intends to exploit with queenside counterplay as quickly as
possible.}  *

