{[%evp 0,36,19,27,68,70,76,37,57,45,37,13,42,35,23,36,20,39,33,24,35,18,55,38,
27,34,26,13,13,44,-15,-98,-98,-259,-259,-245,-271,-271,-307] The Structure 4...
exf6} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bd3
O-O 8. Ne2 Re8 9. Qc2 h5 $1 {This is the new main line in the Classical
Variation. 9...h5 is the move that revives the variation. The move was played
first in 2017, but became extremely popular and nowadays you can find more
than 500 games in the database. The main idea is to stop Ne2-g3. With 4 pawns
around the king, 9...h5 doesn't weaken the kingside that much} (9... h6 10. O-O
Qc7 11. Ng3 $14) (9... g6 10. h4 $36) 10. O-O {The plan with 0-0-0 was covered
in GM Cheparinov's lecture.} h4 11. h3 {White needs to stop h4-h3. Otherwise,
the light squares will be weak later on.} Nd7 12. Be3 Nf8 13. c4 Be6 (13... Bc7
$5 {Is the other option. The idea is Qd6 in the next move}) 14. a3 (14. Rad1 {
Is a better option for White} Rc8 15. Rfe1 Bb8 16. b3 g6 17. Kf1 Kg7 18. Ng1
Qd7 19. Be4 Nh7 20. Qd2 Rcd8 21. d5 cxd5 22. Bxd5 Bxd5 23. Qxd5 Qxd5 24. Rxd5
Rxd5 25. cxd5 Rd8 {1/2-1/2 (25) Solak,D (2594)-Grandelius,N (2651) chess.com
INT 2020}) 14... Qd7 {With the idea of sacrificing the bishop on h3. It is
impossible for White to prevent that.} 15. Qd2 {Diagram [#]} (15. Rfe1 $2 Bxh3
$1) (15. Nf4 $6 Bxf4 16. Bxf4 Qxd4 $15) (15. c5 Bc7 $15) 15... Bxh3 $1 {
Black already obtained a winning position!} 16. gxh3 Qxh3 17. Nf4 Qg4+ 18. Kh2
Ne6 {It is not easy to explain what happened in this game! White was a clear
rating favourite but got destroyed in a miniature. I cannot think of any other
opening line where Black has such an opportunity to outplay White so
effortlessly. Doubtlessly, this game gave Black enormous pleasure!} 0-1

